         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. &amp; zool Garden ¶ 16. May 1860. ¶ My dear Prof. Gray. ¶  ¶ My principle reason for adressing you today consists in bringing under your notice, that a box with dried plants seeds &amp; the las...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.05.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Asa Gray</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Gray Herbarium Archives, Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. &amp; zool Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16. May 1860.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Prof. Gray.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My principle reason for adressing you today consists in bringing under your notice, that a box with dried plants seeds &amp; the last number of my Fragmenta<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Probably Fascicle 12 (B60.05.01), issued in May 1860.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also some sheets of my flora &amp; plates<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Components of B62.03.03. It is not certain how many sheets had been printed by the time of this letter, but sheet K, pp. 73- 80, was printed in June (see M to W. Nicholson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>3 July 1860).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>etc. was forwarded to you under care of Capt. Cate,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Commander of the ship "Black Sea" bound in a few days for New Bedford from Sydney. I regret only, that the collection of plants is not more worthy of your acceptance. — It will however ere long be followed, si fata velint,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If the fates allow.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by a more extensive one.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allways full of immodest wishes for this establishment, I would beg to solicit, that you will kindly send me N.A.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>North American.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Rubi, when in a dormant state, of such species as are close at Hand. They will be both useful &amp; ornamental.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr. Steetz some time since in one of his ingenious &amp; learned letters<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>when with admiration referring to you, says of you: botanicorum facile primus,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Indisputably<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>first among<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>botanists.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a judgment in which I fully concur, &amp; which you fully are entitled to after R. Br.'s labours terminated.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Robert Brown died on 10 June 1858. M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">no doubt</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>mind Alexander von Humboldt's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>description of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Bown as ‘botanicorum facile princeps’<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[indisputably<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the prince of botanists]</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A most excellent &amp; kind friend of mine, Mr. Hooper, a merchant of Melbourne, now permanently returning to the U. States, has kindly taken charge of the elaboration of the extratropical Eucalypti, just issued.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Samuel T.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hoooper of the Boston firm Newell, Hooper &amp; Stephens who opened a commssion agent business in Melbourne and Sydney in 1853<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(circular announcement, 19 January 1853), and operated until 1860, when the Andrew Newell took it over and traded as Newell &amp; Co, (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 1 Febuary 1860, p. 1), but he has not been further identified;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B60.05.01, pp. 32-71.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With my most sincere admiration and attachment, my dear Dr Gray,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">your humble</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Cereus gigantea<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Cereus giganteus</seg>?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has grown beautifully &amp; is now in the possession of many gardens.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cereus gigantea</p>
         </div>
